        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-11-17T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-11-17T19:00:00-05:00" n="847" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d847">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">124.93/11–1749: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to The
                        Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Strong</hi>
                    </persName>), <hi rend="italic">at Chungking</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-11-17T19:00:00-05:00">November 17, 1949—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>TelCan 763. Re Cantel 1288, Nov 17. In view Dept intention close Consulate
                    Kunming immed future, you are instructed to proceed with personnel Emb office to
                    Hong Kong to await further instructions when you consider move from Chungking
                    necessary.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
